headlines.description: — Aaron Holiday scored 20 points, Domantas Sabonis had 16 points, 15 rebounds and six assists in his return from a three-game injury absence and the Indiana Pacers held off the Orlando Magic 111-106 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Holiday, Sabonis lead Pacers past Magic, 111-106

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored a career-high 53 points — including 18 in the fourth quarter and overtime — and the Boston Celtics held on to beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 145-136 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum's career-high 53 help Celtics top T-Wolves 145-136

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — RJ Barrett scored 20 points, making a tiebreaking 3-pointer with 1:15 left in overtime, and the New York Knicks used a late rally to stun the Memphis Grizzlies 133-129 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks rally late, snap Grizzlies' 4-game win streak in OT

headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 42 points, Clint Capela had 22 points and 10 rebounds, and the Atlanta Hawks overcame a sizzling performance by Zach LaVine to beat the Chicago Bulls 120-108 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hawks win 120-108, overcome 50-point game by Bulls' LaVine

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson scored 14 of his 37 points in the fourth quarter and the New Orleans Pelicans held on to beat the Philadelphia 76ers 101-94 on Friday night.
— Miles Bridges scored 26 points to lead the Charlotte Hornets to a 127-119 victory over the Milwaukee Bucks, who were playing Friday night without all five of their usual starters.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges leads Hornets to 127-119 win over short-handed Bucks

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 26 points, 14 assists and 13 rebounds, and the Denver Nuggets held off the San Antonio Spurs for a 121-119 win Friday night when DeMar DeRozan’s tip attempt at the buzzer spun out.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic leads Nuggets to 8th straight win by beating Spurs

events.name: Washington Wizards at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal shook off a sluggish performance and scored six points in the final 6.1 seconds, lifting the Washington Wizards past the Golden State Warriors 110-107 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beal's late heroics lift Wizards past Warriors 110-107

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 31 points, Reggie Jackson added 26 and the Los Angeles Clippers used a dominating second quarter Friday night to defeat the Houston Rockets 126-109 and extend their winning streak to four games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard scores 31 as Clippers extend winning streak to 4
